d to move.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"2\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Not because they had a plan. Not because they knew what was on the other side. But because there was something inside them — a drive, a restlessness, a refusal to stay in the same block — that just kept going. You jumped. You landed somewhere new. You jumped again.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"4\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"And then something happened. A relationship that collapsed around you. A goal that didn't come together the way you imagined. A moment where life revealed that your courage alone is not always enough to protect you from disappointment.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"6\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"And that version of you — the one that moved — went quiet.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"8\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"You didn't call it giving up. You called it being realistic. You called it growing up. You called it understanding how the world actually works. You got busy. You found reasons. You told yourself you'd get back to it next month, next year, when the kids are older, when work calms down, when things are different.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"10\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"But that is what giving up looks like from the inside. It doesn't announce itself. It just slowly, gradually, replaces action with intention. It replaces the doing with the planning-to-do. It replaces the appointment you made with yourself with the perfectly reasonable excuse.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"12\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Here is what I know from working with people at this exact threshold: the version of you that went quiet did not leave.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"14\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"That person got disappointed. They got let down by a plan that didn't hold, by a person who didn't show up the way they said they would, by their own choices in a moment they weren't equipped to navigate differently. And they learned something, in that disappointment, that got filed in the wrong place: I cannot trust myself to see this through.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"16\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"That is the wound underneath the giving up. Not the failure. The loss of trust in your own judgment.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"18\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"And it shows up everywhere after that. In the things you start but don't finish. In the promises you make to yourself that you break quietly, without fanfare, because no one is watching. In the way you perform for other people's approval because somewhere along the way you stopped being able to give it to yourself.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"20\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The brain has a role in this too. It mistakes what is familiar for what is safe. If what is familiar is surviving on less than you deserve, on the narrowest version of your life, on doing just enough to get through — your brain will protect that. It will call growth dangerous. It will call comfort zones home.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"22\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Training rewires that.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"24\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Not motivation. Not a morning playlist. Not a quote on your wall. Training. The deliberate, unglamorous repetition of choosing yourself — even when no one is watching, even when the results aren't visible yet, even when the voice in your head is asking who's going to clap for you at the end.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"26\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Here is the answer to that question: you are.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"28\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"That is not a small thing. It is actually the only thing that works long-term. Because when you learn to applaud yourself, you teach every other person in your life how you are to be treated. Not by telling them. By showing them.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"30\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The version of you that went quiet is not gone. Quiet and gone are not the same thing. One is temporary. One requires grief.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"32\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"This is temporary. What it requires is choice.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"34\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-